#: ../../../getting_started.md:1
msgid "Getting Started"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:3
msgid ""
"New to _Black_? Don't worry, you've found the perfect place to get started!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:5
msgid "Do you like the _Black_ code style?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:7
msgid ""
"Before using _Black_ on some of your code, it might be a good idea to first "
"understand how _Black_ will format your code. _Black_ isn't for everyone and "
"you may find something that is a dealbreaker for you personally, which is "
"okay! The current _Black_ code style [is described here](./"
"the_black_code_style/current_style.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:12
msgid "Try it out quickly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:14
msgid ""
"If you want a quick taste of _Black_ without creating a file first, format a "
"snippet from the command line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:17
msgid "black --code \"x =   {  'a':1,'b':2 }\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:21
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:23
msgid ""
"_Black_ can be installed by running `pip install black`. It requires Python "
"3.10+ to run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:26
msgid "If you use pipx, you can install Black with `pipx install black`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:28
msgid ""
"If you want to format Jupyter Notebooks, install with `pip install "
"\"black[jupyter]\"`. See the [Jupyter Notebooks guide](./guides/"
"using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md) for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:32
msgid ""
"If you can't wait for the latest _hotness_ and want to install from GitHub, "
"use:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:34
msgid "`pip install git+https://github.com/psf/black`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:36
msgid "Basic usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:38
msgid "To get started right away with sensible defaults:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:40
msgid "black {source_file_or_directory}...\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:44
msgid ""
"You can run _Black_ as a package if running it as a script doesn't work:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:46
msgid "python -m black {source_file_or_directory}...\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:50
msgid "Next steps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting_started.md:52
msgid ""
"Took a look at [the _Black_ code style](./the_black_code_style/current_style."
"md) and tried out _Black_? Fantastic, you're ready for more. Why not explore "
"some more on using _Black_ by reading [Usage and Configuration: The basics]"
"(./usage_and_configuration/the_basics.md). Alternatively, you can check out "
"the [Introducing _Black_ to your project](./guides/"
"introducing_black_to_your_project.md) guide."
msgstr ""
